\fs36 About
\fs24 \
This template is designed to produce an essay that adheres to the MLA (Modern Language Association of America) format. However, you should check the exact guidelines of the institution to which you are submitting your paper, as there can be slight variations in expectations (such as whether the first page has a header or not, or whether citations should use italics or underlines). See \'93Adjusting This Template\'94 (below) for information on how to tweak your project to meet your requirements.\
\

\fs36 How To Use This Template
\fs24 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Edit the \'93Title\'94 document so that it contains the title of your essay, your instructor\'92s name and so on.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Compose your essay in text documents inside the \'93Main Content\'94 folder. Whether you use a single document or multiple text files to write your essay is entirely up to you - just make sure they are all inside the \'93Main Content\'94 folder.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Indent block quotes or other special passages using the ruler settings you require in the finished document and enclose them in a \'93Preserve Formatting\'94 block. To do this, select the text of the block quote and go to Format > Formatting > Preserve Formatting. (The quickest way of formatting a block quote is to click in the paragraph and select \'93Essay Block Quote (Preserved)\'94 from the formatting presets, either using the \'93Presets\'85\'94 control in the format bar, or by going to the Format  menu and choosing Formatting > Apply Preset - this will indent the text and apply the \'93Preserve Formatting\'94 block for you.) All other text will have the default MLA indentation assigned during the compile process.\
{\listtext	\'95	}This template includes an \'93Endnotes\'94 document which will be used to hold any footnotes you have created in the main body of the text. If you have not created any footnotes, you should either delete this document or deselect its \'93Include in Compile\'94 setting in the inspector or Compile sheet.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Edit the \'93Works Cited\'94 file so that it contains your own bibliography, being careful to adhere to MLA formatting.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Use File > Compile\'85 to compile your essay for printing.\
