\fs36 Adjusting This Template
\fs24 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}If you require the header to be omitted from the first page and only start on the second, go to the \'93Page Settings\'94 pane in the Compile sheet, click on the \'93Options\'94 tab (next to \'93Header and Footer\'94) and check \'93Different first page header/footer\'94.\
{\listtext	\'95	}This template uses Times New Roman as the font. If you require a different font, such as Arial or Courier, select the text in the \'93Title\'94 and \'93Works Cited\'94 documents and change the font using the font panel or format bar. To change the font for the main body of the text, select the \'93Formatting\'94 tab in the Compile sheet, click on the third row in the table (\'93Level 1+\'94 with the icon of a single text document next to it), and then click into the text area. Finally click on the \'93A\'94 button in the format bar above the text area to choose a different font. To change the header font, select your preferred font in the \'93Page Settings\'94 pane of the Compile sheet.\
